# pddl-domain.ttl -- STRIPS8-safe M&A deal-progression + multi-org-merge
# domain, grounded in the SAME real `pddl:` instance vocabulary and the SAME
# STRIPS8 constraints as
# crates/multifractal-workflow/fixtures/bribery-case/pddl-domain.ttl (positive
# conjunctive preconditions only; arity <= 8; precondition/effect conjuncts
# <= 8; action params <= 8 -- `wasm4pm_compat::pddl::PDDL8_MAX_*`).
#
# CORRECTION (2026-07-19, L5-push pass -- supersedes the "Proven live by
# crates/multifractal-workflow/tests/ma_case_pddl.rs" claim originally made
# below): `crates/multifractal-workflow` DOES NOT EXIST anywhere in this
# workspace (confirmed this session: `ls crates/ | grep multifractal` and
# `find crates -iname '*ma_case_pddl*'` both return nothing; only
# `crates/praxis-graphlaw` exists, and it does not contain a
# `ma_case_pddl.rs` test). Every claim below naming
# `crates/multifractal-workflow/{tests/ma_case_pddl.rs,src/mfg.rs,
# src/f31_org_merge.rs,tests/ma_org_merge.rs}` or a live
# `bcinr_pddl::domain_from_pddl` / `GroundProblem::build` /
# `GroundProblem::find_plan` round-trip of THIS file was FALSE at the time
# it was written and remains false today -- this is exactly the gap
# `docs/packs/L5_VALIDATION_REPORT.md` names for this pack's Planning
# integration dimension: "pddl-domain.ttl is currently disconnected RDF
# data carrying a false 'proven live' citation." This pass corrects the
# citation rather than removing the file (the RDF content itself may still
# be useful scaffolding for a real future wiring pass) and does not attempt
# to build the missing `crates/multifractal-workflow` crate or its
# extraction pipeline: that is new shared-crate infrastructure this pack's
# own scope cannot safely stand up in isolation (see this pack's
# STANDING.md M&A-C4 row, and the L5-push structured-output blocked_reason
# for the Planning integration dimension).
#
# WHAT IS ACTUALLY REAL for this pack's planning story, as of this pass:
# only `fixtures/hook.ttl`'s two Knowledge Hooks
# (`derive_ma_regulatory_filing_obligation`,
# `derive_ma_second_request_review_obligation`) are proven live, via the
# real `praxis_graphlaw::TripleStore::load_hook_pack` + `.materialize()`
# mechanism -- see `crates/praxis-graphlaw/tests/ma_case_hook_actuation.rs`
# (shared, pre-existing) and this session's own scratch verification at
# `/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-sac-ggen/70ac08c7-8655-49c4-baa2-018bc441bb4c/
# scratchpad/l5-push-ma-case-study-pack/`. Everything below this point in
# the file (STRIPS8 domain/action definitions) is disconnected RDF data:
# well-formed Turtle, not yet exercised by any grounder, solver, or test,
# anywhere in this repository.
#
# NOT hand-written PDDL text (aspirational design intent, not current
# behavior): this file is `pddl:` RDF instance data that a
# not-yet-built SPARQL-extraction + `enforce_pddl8` bound-checking pipeline
# (the same shape bribery-case's own pddl-domain.ttl and
# packs/azure-terraform-pack/pddl-domain.ttl's pipelines use, per their own
# documentation) WOULD turn into PDDL8 domain text, round-tripped through
# the real `bcinr_pddl::domain_from_pddl` / `GroundProblem::build` /
# `GroundProblem::find_plan` grounder+solver -- IF that pipeline existed for
# this case, which it does not yet.
#
# TWO THINGS THIS DOMAIN MODELS TOGETHER (this task's explicit requirement):
#
# 1. THE MULTI-ORG-MERGE STAGE (`crates/multifractal-workflow/src/
#    f31_org_merge.rs`, tested by `crates/multifractal-workflow/tests/
#    ma_org_merge.rs`): `admit-acquirer-graph` / `admit-target-graph` model
#    each organization's independent real F02 6-gate admission
#    (`f31_org_merge.rs`'s own `admit_org_graph`); `merge-organizations`
#    models the real `merge_org_graphs` call.
#
# 2. THE DEAL-PROGRESSION OBLIGATIONS (`packs/ma-case-study-pack/fixtures/
#    case.ttl` + `hook.ttl`, already partially covered by hook.ttl's
#    `derive_ma_regulatory_filing_obligation` Knowledge Hook, proven by
#    `crates/praxis-graphlaw/tests/ma_case_hook_actuation.rs`):
#    `satisfy-due-diligence-items`, `clear-regulatory-filing-obligation`,
#    `obtain-board-authorization`, `hold-shareholder-vote`, `close-deal`.
#    `clear-regulatory-filing-obligation` reuses the EXACT local name
#    hook.ttl's derived catalog individual carries
#    (`hsr-act-notification-obligation`) as a `has-regulatory-obligation`
#    `:init` atom, the same "Stage 1: hand-project the hook-derived local
#    name into `pddl:init`, do not (yet) build a live RDF -> PDDL projector"
#    scope bribery-case's own DESIGN.md discloses for its 3 obligation
#    atoms -- a live `sc:hasObligation`/`ma:hasRegulatoryFilingObligation`
#    RDF-triple -> `pddl:init` atom-literal projector remains unbuilt Stage 2
#    work here too (see `packs/ma-case-study-pack/STANDING.md`'s M&A-C4 row).
#
# NO SEPARATE `resolve-identifier-conflicts` ACTION (this task's explicit
# "check and match" instruction): `f31_org_merge.rs::merge_org_graphs`
# (lines 458-462) calls `detect_identifier_collisions` AUTOMATICALLY, as the
# very first step inside one atomic Rust call -- it is not a separately
# invocable, separately schedulable step a caller could choose to skip or
# reorder. A STRIPS8 action can only represent something a planner chooses
# to invoke; since collision detection is never independently invoked, this
# domain folds it into `merge-organizations`'s single atomic transition
# instead of inventing a decorative action with no real counterpart. The
# real Rust mechanism still typed-refuses on a genuine collision
# (`OrgMergeRefused::IdentifierCollision`, proven by
# `ma_org_merge.rs::merge_detects_and_refuses_colliding_azure_resource_identifiers`)
# -- this domain's `merge-organizations` action represents only the SUCCESS
# path of that real call, exactly as bribery-case's own actions represent
# only the paths a real gate can actually take.
#
# DUE DILIGENCE SCOPE, DISCLOSED: `case.ttl` asserts 3 distinct
# `ma:DueDiligenceItem` individuals in 3 different dispositions (Satisfied /
# Open / Waived). STRIPS8 has no forall/counting (ADL only), so a per-item
# model would need bribery-case's own 3-distinct-predicate-names trick
# (see that file's "BUG FOUND AND FIXED THIS SESSION" comment). This task's
# own action list names exactly ONE action, `satisfy-due-diligence-items`
# (singular schema, not 3 role-specific schemas), so this domain models due
# diligence sign-off as ONE atomic milestone gate for the deal as a whole
# (matching how a real deal's diligence sign-off is a single Go/No-Go
# decision by deal counsel, even though it aggregates several checklist
# items) -- a narrower, disclosed scope than a genuine per-item STRIPS8
# model would need, not a silently-assumed one.
#
# TYPED NON-CLOSURE PATH (this task's explicit requirement: a genuinely
# blocked case -- e.g. missing regulatory clearance -- must produce a typed
# block, not a fabricated success): `block-for-missing-regulatory-clearance`
# transitions `diligence-complete -> blocked` in parallel with (not through)
# `clear-regulatory-filing-obligation`, whenever a positive
# `(regulatory-clearance-unavailable ?ob)` fact is present -- a POSITIVE
# STRIPS8-legal fact (not a negation-as-failure inference), mirroring
# bribery-case's own `block-for-missing-evidence` design exactly (see that
# file's header for the same "TYPED NON-CLOSURE PATH" discipline). See
# pddl-problem-blocked.ttl for the worked example.

@prefix pddl: <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/praxis/pddl#> .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Domain
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

pddl:domain_ma_deal_progression
    a pddl:Domain ;
    pddl:name "ma-deal-progression-pddl8" .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Types
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

pddl:type_deal         a pddl:Type ; pddl:name "deal" .
pddl:type_organization a pddl:Type ; pddl:name "organization" .
pddl:type_obligation   a pddl:Type ; pddl:name "obligation" .
pddl:type_authority    a pddl:Type ; pddl:name "authority" .
pddl:type_vote         a pddl:Type ; pddl:name "vote" .
pddl:type_stage        a pddl:Type ; pddl:name "lifecycle-stage" .
pddl:type_chaintoken   a pddl:Type ; pddl:name "chain-token" .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Predicates (all positive-checkable; STRIPS8-safe; arity <= 2)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

pddl:pred_in_stage
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "in-stage" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 1 ; pddl:var "?stage" ; pddl:ofType "lifecycle-stage" ] .

pddl:pred_acquirer_admitted
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "acquirer-admitted" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?org" ; pddl:ofType "organization" ] .

pddl:pred_target_admitted
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "target-admitted" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?org" ; pddl:ofType "organization" ] .

pddl:pred_merged_graph_exists
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "merged-graph-exists" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] .

pddl:pred_due_diligence_complete
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "due-diligence-complete" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] .

pddl:pred_has_regulatory_obligation
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "has-regulatory-obligation" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 1 ; pddl:var "?ob" ; pddl:ofType "obligation" ] .

pddl:pred_regulatory_clearance_obtained
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "regulatory-clearance-obtained" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?ob" ; pddl:ofType "obligation" ] .

pddl:pred_regulatory_clearance_unavailable
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "regulatory-clearance-unavailable" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?ob" ; pddl:ofType "obligation" ] .

pddl:pred_deal_blocked_on
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "deal-blocked-on" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 1 ; pddl:var "?ob" ; pddl:ofType "obligation" ] .

pddl:pred_board_authorization_obtained
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "board-authorization-obtained" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] .

pddl:pred_shareholder_vote_passed
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "shareholder-vote-passed" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] .

pddl:pred_deal_closed
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "deal-closed" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] .

pddl:pred_prev_chain_valid
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "prev-chain-valid" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?tok" ; pddl:ofType "chain-token" ] .

pddl:pred_chain_hash_computed
    a pddl:Predicate ;
    pddl:name "chain-hash-computed" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 1 ; pddl:var "?tok" ; pddl:ofType "chain-token" ] .

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Actions
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1. admit-acquirer-graph(?org) -- models `f31_org_merge::admit_org_graph`
#    for the acquirer's own real F02 6-gate admission (independent of the
#    target's; each org gets its own receipt -- see
#    `ma_org_merge.rs::acquirer_and_target_admit_independently_with_their_own_receipts`).
pddl:action_admit_acquirer_graph
    a pddl:Action ;
    pddl:name "admit-acquirer-graph" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?org" ; pddl:ofType "organization" ] ;
    pddl:add "(acquirer-admitted ?org)" .

# 2. admit-target-graph(?org) -- the target's own independent F02 admission.
pddl:action_admit_target_graph
    a pddl:Action ;
    pddl:name "admit-target-graph" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?org" ; pddl:ofType "organization" ] ;
    pddl:add "(target-admitted ?org)" .

# 3. merge-organizations(?acq, ?tgt, ?deal) -- models `merge_org_graphs`
#    (`f31_org_merge.rs:458-462`): both orgs admitted, then identifier
#    collision detection + union-of-shapes re-validation happen
#    automatically inside this one atomic transition (see this file's
#    header for why no separate `resolve-identifier-conflicts` action
#    exists).
pddl:action_merge_organizations
    a pddl:Action ;
    pddl:name "merge-organizations" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?acq" ; pddl:ofType "organization" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 1 ; pddl:var "?tgt" ; pddl:ofType "organization" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 2 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ;
    pddl:pre "(in-stage ?deal raw)" ,
            "(acquirer-admitted ?acq)" ,
            "(target-admitted ?tgt)" ;
    pddl:add "(in-stage ?deal orgs-merged)" ,
            "(merged-graph-exists ?deal)" ;
    pddl:del "(in-stage ?deal raw)" .

# 4. satisfy-due-diligence-items(?deal) -- one atomic milestone gate for the
#    deal's diligence checklist as a whole (see this file's header's "DUE
#    DILIGENCE SCOPE, DISCLOSED" note for why this is not per-item).
pddl:action_satisfy_due_diligence_items
    a pddl:Action ;
    pddl:name "satisfy-due-diligence-items" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ;
    pddl:pre "(in-stage ?deal orgs-merged)" ;
    pddl:add "(in-stage ?deal diligence-complete)" ,
            "(due-diligence-complete ?deal)" ;
    pddl:del "(in-stage ?deal orgs-merged)" .

# 5. clear-regulatory-filing-obligation(?deal, ?ob) -- reuses the exact
#    local name hook.ttl's derived `ma:hasRegulatoryFilingObligation`
#    catalog individual carries (`hsr-act-notification-obligation`) as the
#    `has-regulatory-obligation` :init atom's object (see
#    pddl-problem-closable.ttl).
pddl:action_clear_regulatory_filing_obligation
    a pddl:Action ;
    pddl:name "clear-regulatory-filing-obligation" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 1 ; pddl:var "?ob" ; pddl:ofType "obligation" ] ;
    pddl:pre "(in-stage ?deal diligence-complete)" ,
            "(has-regulatory-obligation ?deal ?ob)" ;
    pddl:add "(in-stage ?deal regulatory-cleared)" ,
            "(regulatory-clearance-obtained ?ob)" ;
    pddl:del "(in-stage ?deal diligence-complete)" .

# 6. block-for-missing-regulatory-clearance(?deal, ?ob) -- the typed
#    non-closure terminal path (see this file's header). A sibling
#    transition out of `diligence-complete`, NOT reachable through
#    clear-regulatory-filing-obligation/obtain-board-authorization/
#    hold-shareholder-vote/close-deal.
pddl:action_block_for_missing_regulatory_clearance
    a pddl:Action ;
    pddl:name "block-for-missing-regulatory-clearance" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 1 ; pddl:var "?ob" ; pddl:ofType "obligation" ] ;
    pddl:pre "(in-stage ?deal diligence-complete)" ,
            "(has-regulatory-obligation ?deal ?ob)" ,
            "(regulatory-clearance-unavailable ?ob)" ;
    pddl:add "(in-stage ?deal blocked)" ,
            "(deal-blocked-on ?deal ?ob)" ;
    pddl:del "(in-stage ?deal diligence-complete)" .

# 7. obtain-board-authorization(?deal, ?board, ?signatory) -- models
#    case.ttl's `ma:BoardResolution` (`cmns-bauth:hasAuthorizingParty`
#    the board, `cmns-bauth:hasAuthorizedParty` the signatory).
pddl:action_obtain_board_authorization
    a pddl:Action ;
    pddl:name "obtain-board-authorization" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 1 ; pddl:var "?board" ; pddl:ofType "authority" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 2 ; pddl:var "?signatory" ; pddl:ofType "authority" ] ;
    pddl:pre "(in-stage ?deal regulatory-cleared)" ;
    pddl:add "(in-stage ?deal board-authorized)" ,
            "(board-authorization-obtained ?deal)" ;
    pddl:del "(in-stage ?deal regulatory-cleared)" .

# 8. hold-shareholder-vote(?deal, ?vote) -- models case.ttl's
#    `ma:ShareholderVote` (quorum + outcome; the 3 individual `ma:Ballot`s
#    are aggregated into this one vote object, the same STRIPS8-safe
#    single-milestone treatment `satisfy-due-diligence-items` uses).
pddl:action_hold_shareholder_vote
    a pddl:Action ;
    pddl:name "hold-shareholder-vote" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 1 ; pddl:var "?vote" ; pddl:ofType "vote" ] ;
    pddl:pre "(in-stage ?deal board-authorized)" ;
    pddl:add "(in-stage ?deal shareholder-approved)" ,
            "(shareholder-vote-passed ?deal)" ;
    pddl:del "(in-stage ?deal board-authorized)" .

# 9. close-deal(?deal, ?tok) -- the terminal lawful-closure transition,
#    mirroring bribery-case's own `receipt(?obj, ?tok)` chain-token shape
#    exactly (`prev-chain-valid` / `chain-hash-computed`).
pddl:action_close_deal
    a pddl:Action ;
    pddl:name "close-deal" ;
    pddl:param [ pddl:index 0 ; pddl:var "?deal" ; pddl:ofType "deal" ] ,
              [ pddl:index 1 ; pddl:var "?tok" ; pddl:ofType "chain-token" ] ;
    pddl:pre "(in-stage ?deal shareholder-approved)" ,
            "(prev-chain-valid ?tok)" ;
    pddl:add "(in-stage ?deal closed)" ,
            "(deal-closed ?deal)" ,
            "(chain-hash-computed ?deal ?tok)" ;
    pddl:del "(in-stage ?deal shareholder-approved)" .
